<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10486001>
    dc:description "Fig. 2. Maximum absorbance (300–500 nm) chromatograms from LC–UV analyses of 80% CH3OH extracts of Magnolia tepals (top to bottom): M. salicifolia (BI-19354), M. kobus (BI-19363), M. virginiana (BI-19682), M. sieboldii (BI-19731), M. macrophylla (BI-19560), M. delavayi (BI-19737) and M. acuminata (BI-20613). Peaks labelled the phenylethanoid glycosides 1–6 and the 3-O-rutinosides of quercetin (a), kaempferol (b) and isorhamnetin (c). The peak next to 2 in M. virginiana is an isomer of 2 that was not investigated further." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10486001/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

